SUFFIX_ONE = 'st'
SUFFIX_TWO = 'nd'
SUFFIX_THREE = 'rd'
SUFFIX_OTHER = 'th'

def what_century(year):
    century = 1 + (int(year) - 1) // 100
    return str(century) + ordinal_suffix(century)

def ordinal_suffix(number):
    if number // 10 == 1:   # ten or teen
        return SUFFIX_OTHER
    elif number % 10 == 1:  # ending 1
        return SUFFIX_ONE
    elif number % 10 == 2:  # ending 2
        return SUFFIX_TWO
    elif number % 10 == 3:  # ending 3
        return SUFFIX_THREE
    else:
        return SUFFIX_OTHER

def what_century(year):
    year = int(year)
    output_century = year // 100
    ordinal = ''

    if year % 100 > 0: output_century += 1

    if output_century > 10 and output_century < 14: ordinal = 'th'
    elif output_century % 10 == 1: ordinal = 'st'
    elif output_century % 10 == 2: ordinal = 'nd'
    elif output_century % 10 == 3: ordinal = 'rd'
    else: ordinal = 'th'

    return str(output_century) + ordinal
